  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nCurrently, if a `password.txt` file is within the same folder as the keystores JSON within `./keystores`, there is a fatal error that persists.\r\n\r\n```\r\nJun-04 23:08:02.054[]                 info: Lodestar network=prater, version=v0.38.0-dev.b5e24f7138, commit=b5e24f71389092c965e00b2c4c80c511d72fc4b1\r\n âœ– SyntaxError: Error parsing keystore at /keystores/password.txt: Unexpected token Y in JSON at position 0\r\n    at JSON.parse (<anonymous>)\r\n    at Function.parse (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/bls-keystore/lib/class.js:53:41)\r\n    at file:///usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar-cli/src/cmds/validator/keys.ts:68:31\r\n    at Array.map (<anonymous>)\r\n    at getLocalSecretKeys (file:///usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar-cli/src/cmds/validator/keys.ts:63:21)\r\n    at Object.validatorHandler [as handler] (file:///usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar-cli/src/cmds/validator/handler.ts:65:50)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n`password.txt` should be able to be read within the `./keystores` folder. Should not cause fatal error.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n<!--Steps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Have validator `keystores.json` inside `./keystores` folder.\r\n2. Have `password.txt` file also inside the `./keystores` folder. \r\n3. Run the validator client.\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n<img width=\"1063\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-06-04 at 5 13 21 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58080811/172028395-3b393b3f-a581-46b1-9c69-c388667b7db3.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"743\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-06-04 at 5 13 40 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58080811/172028400-167e0a71-b0dd-4d48-a79a-d29c89472ab2.png\">\r\n",
